{SOUTH makes a positive 3\H response to NORTH's 2\C opener. 
This promises at least 8 points and a 5-card suit with two or more honors.

NORTH only needs to know one thing - how many Aces in the SOUTH hand. 
A Blackwood 4NT tells her the answer is one, so she bids 6\H.}

