[Student "S"]
{When NORTH opens 1NT, point-count alone tells SOUTH that 6NT can surely be made. 
NORTH is bound to hold at least two Aces. But SOUTH doesn't want to miss a Grand slam.

SOUTH bids 4\C, (Gerber), and NORTH admits to just two Aces. 

So SOUTH settles for the small slam.}

